text: Jefferson County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,663. The county seat is Fairfield. The county was founded in January 1839, and was named after U.S. President Thomas Jefferson.Jefferson County == References == Category:1830s establishments in Iowa Territory Category:1839 establishments in the United States Category:Iowa counties
title: Jefferson County, Iowa
